WHEREAS, since 1985, Louisiana and Taiwan have maintained a sister-state
relationship and enjoy particularly close economic ties; and
WHEREAS, Louisiana and the Unites States have benefitted immeasurably through
decades of unwavering friendship with Taiwan and the wider world is sure to reap
tremendous rewards as Taiwan works to enhance its presence in the international
community.
THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Legislature of Louisiana does hereby
express support for strengthening our partnership with Taiwan, for the expansion of Taiwan's
role on the global stage, and for its efforts to preserve peace and stability in the Taiwan Strait
through meaningful dialogue.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Legislature of Louisiana supports a tax
agreement between the United States and Taiwan, supports the goals of the Critical Undersea
Infrastructure Resilience Initiative Act to prioritize the protection and resilience of undersea
cables near Taiwan, with a focus on countering gray zone tactics from the People's Republic
of China, and maintains that United Nations General Assembly Resolution 2758 cannot be
used to exclude Taiwan from participation in the United Nations System and other
international fora such as the International Civil Aviation Organization, the International
Criminal Police Organization, and the United Nations Framework Convention on Climate
Change.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Legislature of Louisiana celebrates the
forty-seventh anniversary of the Taiwan Relations Act and the forty-first anniversary of the
sister-state relationship between the state of Louisiana and Taiwan.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that a copy of this Resolution be transmitted to the
Taipei Economic and Cultural Office in Houston.
